## Steps

### step 1
id: open-batch
instruction: On the Batches page, click on the batch that has finished processing — it shows "Needs Review" status.
success_criteria: You are on the Batch Review page. The header shows the batch name, status, and a claim count summary broken down by severity (Clean, Advisory, Warning, Blocking).
anchor: "Needs Review"
on_success: next
on_stuck: Find a batch card with a "Needs Review" status badge and click on it.

### step 2
id: read-claim-summary
instruction: Review the claim severity summary in the header to understand the scope — how many claims are clean, have advisories, warnings, or blocking issues.
success_criteria: You can see a breakdown of claims by severity (e.g., "39 Clean, 5 Advisory, 3 Blocking").
anchor: "claim count"
on_success: next
on_stuck: The claim counts appear in the header area of the Batch Review page as colored badges.

### step 3
id: click-review-edits
instruction: Click "Review Edits" in the four-step workflow checklist to enter the edit carousel.
success_criteria: The edit carousel has opened showing the first flagged issue — which claims are affected, why it was flagged, and the likely fix.
anchor: "Review Edits"
on_success: next
on_stuck: The "Review Edits" button is part of a four-step workflow checklist on the Batch Review page.

### step 4
id: navigate-through-issues
instruction: Read each issue carefully and use the carousel navigation to move through all flagged issues. Use the Altair chat sidebar if you need help understanding any edit.
success_criteria: You have reviewed all flagged issues in the carousel.
anchor: "next issue"
on_success: next
on_stuck: Use the arrow buttons on the carousel to navigate between issues.

### step 5
id: fix-claims-externally
instruction: Make the necessary corrections in your practice management system and export a new 837 file with those fixes applied.
success_criteria: You have a corrected 837 file ready to upload.
anchor: "Fix in your practice management system"
on_success: next
on_stuck: This step happens outside Altair in your billing software. Make the corrections, export a new 837, then return here.

### step 6
id: reupload-corrected-batch
instruction: Click "Re-upload corrected batch" (Step 3 of the workflow checklist) and upload your corrected file.
success_criteria: Altair compares the new file to the original and a summary card shows what changed. Any edits your corrections addressed are automatically resolved.
anchor: "Re-upload corrected batch"
on_success: completion
on_stuck: The re-upload button is in Step 3 of the workflow checklist on the Batch Review page.

## Completion Message
nice work — altair compared your corrected file and resolved the issues you fixed. if any blocking issues remain, address them in step 4 before releasing. want me to walk you through releasing the batch?

